Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi says the Border Management Authority will ultimately take over the management of borders once it's fully operational. Moloko Moloto reports. #dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - The days of lawlessness on our borders are over. This is according to Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi who unveiled the first 200 cohort of border guards hired to secure the country's borders. WATCH | Minister Motsoaledi speaks on SA border patrols Speaking at the Beitbridge Border Post, Motsoaledi says the Border Management Authority (BMA) will ultimately take over the management of borders once it's fully operational. Motsoaledi says the mandate of border guards and the BMA isn’t to stop people from entering South Africa but to ensure they do so legally. * eNCA's Moloko Moloto reports.